{
  "doc_id": "60809",
  "text": "The notion of eleven-dimensional M-theory emerged [CITATION_1] as the strong-coupling limit of IIA superstring theory. More precisely, M-theory compactified on a (space-like) circle of radius R 11 is identical to IIA superstring theory with coupling g s = R 11 / √ α ′ . While this sounds like a mere definition, the non-trivial conjecture is that in the g s → ∞ limit, the resulting theory has eleven-dimensional Lorenz invariance. Once one accepts this conjecture, a statement about M-theory can be translated into a statement about IIA superstring theory at generic coupling.",
